AN ACT relating to elections; requiring a candidate at a presidential
preference primary election to pay a filing fee; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 In a presidential election year, existing law requires, with certain exceptions,
2 that a presidential preference primary election be held to determine the preferences
3 of the registered voters of a major political party regarding the party’s nominee for
4 President of the United States. (NRS 298.600-298.720) A person who is a qualified
5 candidate to be a major political party’s nominee for President of the United States
6 and wants to appear on the ballot for a presidential preference primary election
7 must file with the Secretary of State a declaration of candidacy. (NRS 298.660)
8 Existing law also requires certain persons to pay a filing fee for filing a declaration
9 of candidacy for certain federal, state and local offices. (NRS 293.193)
10 Sections 1 and 2 of this bill require a person who files a declaration of
11 candidacy for the presidential preference primary election to pay a filing fee of
12 $1,000.
